In the antibacterial tests, five types of glass microbeads were used (please kindly refer to Table 1
                        ). The surface modification of the glass microbeads (GD2–5) was monitored using FT-IR spectroscopy (Fig. 4
                        ), SEM (Fig. 5
                        ), and fluorescence microscopy (Fig. 6
                        ).

Three types of chitosan microbeads were tested - plain, crosslinked, and carbon dots-coated (Table 1). The surface modification of the chitosan microbeads (GD6–8) was monitored using FT-IR spectroscopy (Fig. 8
                        ) and SEM (Fig. 9
                        ).
